Effectively Final

--Lambda's are allowed to use local variables but not allowed to modify it even though they are not declared final.
 this concept is called EFFECTIVELY FINAL.

 - Not allowed to modify the value inside the lambda.
-   reassigning not allowed

 --Prior to JAva-8, any variable that's used inside the anonymous class should be declared final.



-- Advantage of Effectively Final --

- Easy to perform concurrency operations..
- Promotes functional programming and demotes the imperative style of programming.